The hydraulic energy of the pressurized concentrated water ( brine ) flowing out of the RO module is recovered by a specific hydraulic cylinder ( main actuator in
Figure 1
) , which enables it to pump and fill the low-pressure reservoir with saltwater .

A second hydraulic actuator ( refiling actuator in
Figure 1
) is used to transfer the working fluid from the low-pressure condenser to the high-pressure evaporator .
